      "rationale": "Blood viscosity modeled as Newtonian (mu = 0.0035 Pa·s) based on published consensus values for shear rates above 100 s-1 in CPB conditions. Density 1050 kg/m3. Inlet boundary conditions derived from experimental flow meter measurements. All inputs documented with traceability. Uncertainty quantification was performed across inlet flow rate (±5%), rotational speed (±1%), and blood viscosity (±8%) using Monte Carlo sampling (n=500); a screening sensitivity study described in the UQ report narrative identified viscosity and flow rate as the largest contributors to hemolysis index variance. Model inputs level 2 met."
